# Flask Chat App with Amazon Bedrock and AWS Secrets Manager

This Flask chat application interacts with the Mistral 7B Instruct model via Amazon Bedrock. It securely retrieves AWS credentials from AWS Secrets Manager to interact with the model.

## Features

- Chat interface to interact with the Mistral 7B Instruct model
- Secure handling of AWS credentials using AWS Secrets Manager
- Containerized using Docker for easy deployment

## Prerequisites

- Python 3.9 or higher
- Docker and Docker Compose
- AWS account with access to Amazon Bedrock and Secrets Manager

## Setup

### 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/flask-chat-app.git
cd flask-chat-app


# BUILD USING DOCKER
docker build -t flask-chat-app .

docker-compose up --build

